examples.en: The lake was rippled by a sailboat.
The sailboat was adrift on the open sea.
Fierce winds buffeted the small sailboat.
We were stuck in the sailboat for an hour until the wind came up and we could move again.
They righted the sailboat that had capsized.
A huge wave out of nowhere caused our little sailboat to capsize.
Since the wind had completely died, they had to oar the sailboat back to shore...
